Description: Ring foot and wall sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery open vessel (bowl?); glazed black on interior, exterior and inner face of foot; reserved: resting surface and underside; circle in dilute glaze on underside; inscription incised on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 485)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1870)
